The paper deals with graph theory and specifically with the problem of constructing a graph that contains all possible forests of a certain size as induced subgraphs. This problem is related to topics such as discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and distributed computing (cs.DL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
